The Chronicle Ricky Zililo, Senior Sports Reporter REGISTRATION for the four regional Division One land Two leagues will start from May 1-31. The Central, Eastern, Northern and Southern bosses agreed at a meeting held in Kwekwe on Saturday to resume competition. They proposed that league games start on June 12, a month after the Premier Soccer League’s restart. The topflight league is scheduled to kick-off on May 15. “League games resume on June 12-13. This will be a month after the PSL programme would have resumed as indicated in the Sports and Recreation Commission’s initial directives that lower leagues would resume a month after the PSL. “The season is expected to end in the second week of December,” reads a message sent to clubs. – @ZililoR